On the National Day for the Victims of Communism, the United States remembers the more than 100 million people who have died due to communist oppression. The day coincides with the 30th anniversary of the fall of the Berlin Wall, symbolizing the triumph of democracy over tyranny. The US reaffirms its commitment to promoting peace and prosperity based on democratic principles and human rights. It vows to work with allies and partners to ensure freedom prevails worldwide and to protect the cherished liberties that foster peace and prosperity. Together, a future free from the evils of communism can be built.